Assets Loans And Receivables Amounts Receivable From Clients Outstanding Security Settlements Amount

For those institutions that have broking activity (i.e. equity broking) with clients who are other than financial institutions, record the amount due from clients in relation to security settlement transactions. Do not include amounts receivable from financial institutions or clearing houses in relation to security settlements.
Assets Loans And Receivables Credit Cards Gross General Reserve For Credit Losses Amount
The general reserve for credit losses applying to the gross value of credit cards.
Assets Loans And Receivables Credit Cards Gross Of Provisions Denominated In AUD Amount
Total gross loans and advances denominated in Australian dollars (Gross of specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses) applying to the gross value of credit cards.
Assets Loans And Receivables Credit Cards Gross Of Provisions Denominated In Foreign Currency Amount
Total gross loans and advances denominated other than in Australian dollars (Gross of specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses) applying to the gross value of credit cards.
Assets Loans And Receivables Credit Cards Gross Specific Provisions Amount
The specific provisions for impairment applying to the gross value of credit cards.
Assets Loans And Receivables Credit Cards Gross Total Amount
The gross value of credit cards gross of any specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses.
Assets Loans And Receivables Housing Fixed Rate Gross General Reserve For Credit Losses Amount
The general reserve for credit losses applying to the gross value of fixed interest rate housing loans.
Assets Loans And Receivables Housing Fixed Rate Gross Of Provisions Denominated in AUD Amount
Total gross loans and advances denominated in Australian dollars (Gross of specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses) applying to the gross value of fixed interest rate housing loans.
Assets Loans And Receivables Housing Fixed Rate Gross Of Provisions Denominated in Foreign Currency Amount

Total gross loans and advances denominated other than in Australian dollars (Gross of specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses) applying to the gross value of fixed interest rate housing loans.
Assets Loans And Receivables Housing Fixed Rate Gross Specific Provisions Amount
The specific provisions for impairment applying to the gross value of fixed interest rate housing loans.
Assets Loans And Receivables Housing Fixed Rate Gross Total Amount
The gross value of fixed interest rate housing loans gross of any specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses.
Assets Loans And Receivables Housing Variable Rate Gross General Reserve For Credit Losses Amount
The general reserve for credit losses applying to the gross value of variable interest rate housing loans.
Assets Loans And Receivables Housing Variable Rate Gross Specific Provisions Amount
The specific provisions for impairment applying to the gross value of variable interest rate housing loans.
Assets Loans And Receivables Housing Variable Rate Gross Of Provisions Denominated in AUD Amount

Total gross loans and advances denominated in Australian dollars (Gross of specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses) applying to the gross value of variable interest rate housing loans.
Assets Loans And Receivables Housing Variable Rate Gross Of Provisions Denominated in Foreign Currency Amount

Total gross loans and advances denominated other than in Australian dollars (Gross of specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses) applying to the gross value of variable interest rate housing loans.
Assets Loans And Receivables Housing Variable Rate Gross Total Amount
The gross value of variable interest rate housing loans gross of any specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses.
Assets Loans And Receivables Interest Bearing Loans Amount
Gross amounts loaned or advanced for which an interest component is being charged.
Assets Loans And Receivables Interest Free Loans Amount
Gross amounts loaned or advanced for which no interest component is being charge
Assets Loans And Receivables Lease Financing Gross General Reserve For Credit Losses Amount
The general reserve for credit losses applying to the gross value of lease financing.
Assets Loans And Receivables Lease Financing Gross Of Provisions Denominated In AUD Amount
Total gross loans and advances representing lease financing that is denominated in Australian dollars is reported net of unearned revenue and gross of provisions.
Assets Loans And Receivables Lease Financing Gross Of Provisions Denominated In Foreign Currency Amount
Total gross loans and advances representing lease financing that is denominated other than in Australian dollars is reported net of unearned revenue and gross of provisions.
Assets Loans And Receivables Lease Financing Gross Specific Provisions Amount
The specific provisions for impairment applying to the gross value of lease financing.
Assets Loans And Receivables Lease Financing Gross Total Amount
Total gross loans and advances representing lease financing is reported net of unearned revenue and gross of provisions.
Assets Loans And Receivables Loans And Advances Gross General Reserve for Credit Losses Amount
Record the General Reserve for Credit Losses applying to the total loan portfolio.
Assets Loans And Receivables Loans And Advances Gross Of Provisions Denominated In AUD Amount
Total gross loans and advances denominated in Australian dollars - Gross of specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses
Assets Loans And Receivables Loans And Advances Gross Of Provisions Denominated In Foreign Currency Amount
Total gross loans and advances denominated other than in Australian dollars - Gross of specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses
Assets Loans And Receivables Loans And Advances Gross Specific Provisions Amount

Record the specific provisions applying to the total loan portfolio. Where an ADI adopts a standardised approach under APS 220 (paragraph 11), as described in AGN 220.3, the value of the prescribed provision should also be included here.
Assets Loans And Receivables Loans And Advances Gross Total Amount
The value of loans and advances gross of specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses
Assets Loans And Receivables Loans And Advances Net Available For Sale Amount
Total Gross Loans and Advances, held available for sale, less Deferred Fee Income, Specific Provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses
Assets Loans And Receivables Loans And Advances Net Denominated In Foreign Currency Amount

Of the total amount reported for Net loans and advances (net of provisions for impairment and General Reserve for Credit Losses) identify the component that is denominated in a foreign currency. Report the Australian dollar equivalent of this foreign currency amount.
Assets Loans And Receivables Loans And Advances Net Total Amount
Total Loans and Advances net of provisions and unearned revenue.
Assets Loans And Receivables Net Amount

Net Loans and Receivables balances categorised in accordance with AASB 139 and compliant with the prerequisite for netting outlined in Australian accounting standards AASB 139, AASB 7, and AASB 132 Financial Instruments: Disclosure and Presentation and any relevant prudential standards.
Assets Loans And Receivables Other Domestic Financial Institutions Gross Of Provisions Denominated in Foreign Currency Amount

Include the gross value of loans that are denominated other than in Australian dollars to Financial corporations other than: Central borrowing authorities, Other insurance corps, Pension funds, Life insurance corps, Registered financial corps, Other ADIs, Banks, Foreign central banks, RBA.

The general reserve for credit losses applying to the total loans and advances other than: Total Gross Lease financing, Total Gross Term loan - fixed rate, Total Gross Term loan - variable rate, Total Gross Housing - fixed rate, Total Gross Housing - variable rate, Total Gross Credit cards, Total Gross Revolving credit.
Assets Loans And Receivables Other Loans And Advances Consolidated Gross Specific Provisions Amount

The specific provisions for impairment applying to the total loans and advances other than: Total Gross Lease financing, Total Gross Term loan - fixed rate, Total Gross Term loan - variable rate, Total Gross Housing - fixed rate, Total Gross Housing - variable rate, Total Gross Credit cards, Total Gross Revolving credit.
Assets Loans And Receivables Other Loans And Advances Consolidated Gross Total Amount

This is the balancing item of the total loans and advances other than: Total Gross Lease financing, Total Gross Term loan - fixed rate, Total Gross Term loan - variable rate, Total Gross Housing - fixed rate, Total Gross Housing - variable rate, Total Gross Credit cards, Total Gross Revolving credit
Assets Loans And Receivables Other Loans And Advances Loans Held For Sale Gross General Reserve For Credit Losses Amount
The general reserve for credit losses applying to the gross value of loans held for sale.
Assets Loans And Receivables Other Loans And Advances Loans Held For Sale Gross of Provisions Denominated In AUD Amount
Total gross loans and advances representing loans held for sale that are denominated in Australian dollars is reported gross of provisions.
Assets Loans And Receivables Other Loans And Advances Loans Held For Sale Gross of Provisions Denominated In Foreign Currency Amount
Total gross loans and advances representing loans held for sale that are denominated other than in Australian dollars is reported gross of provisions.
Assets Loans And Receivables Other Loans And Advances Loans Held For Sale Gross Specific Provisions Amount
The specific provisions for impairment applying to the gross value of loans held for sale.
Assets Loans And Receivables Other Loans And Advances Loans Held For Sale Gross Total Amount

Total gross loans and advances representing loans held for sale gross of provisions. Loans held for sale are loans (e.g. mortgages) acquired and held by the reporting party with the intention of resale in the short-term (i.e. within 12 months of acquisition) in accordance with AASB 5.

Assets Loans And Receivables Other Loans And Advances Margin Lending Gross of Provisions Denominated In AUD Amount

Assets Loans And Receivables Other Loans And Advances Margin Lending Gross of Provisions Denominated In Foreign Currency Amount
Total gross loans and advances representing margin lending that are denominated other than in Australian dollars is reported gross of provisions.
Assets Loans And Receivables Other Loans And Advances Margin Lending Gross Specific Provisions Amount
The specific provisions for impairment applying to the gross value of margin lending.
Assets Loans And Receivables Other Loans And Advances Margin Lending Gross Total Amount

Total gross loans and advances representing margin lending gross of provisions. Lending for the purpose of purchasing equities, where the underlying security is equities. Report all loans of the loan portfolio meeting these criteria.

Total Margin lending Total Loans held for sale
Assets Loans And Receivables Other Loans And Advances Other Gross of Provisions Denominated In Foreign Currency Amount

Total gross loans and advances denominated other than in Australian dollars (Gross of specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses) other than: Total Gross Lease financing, Total Gross Term loan - fixed rate, Total Gross Term loan - variable rate, Total Gross Housing - fixed rate, Total Gross Housing - variable rate, Total Gross Credit cards, Total Gross Revolving credit. Total Margin lending Total Loans held for sale
Assets Loans And Receivables Other Loans And Advances Other Gross Specific Provisions Amount

The specific provisions for impairment applying to the total loans and advances other than: Total Gross Lease financing, Total Gross Term loan - fixed rate, Total Gross Term loan - variable rate, Total Gross Housing - fixed rate, Total Gross Housing - variable rate, Total Gross Credit cards, Total Gross Revolving credit Total Margin lending Total Loans held for sale
Assets Loans And Receivables Other Loans And Advances Other Gross Total Amount

This is the balancing item of the total loans and advances other than: Total Gross Lease financing, Total Gross Term loan - fixed rate, Total Gross Term loan - variable rate, Total Gross Housing - fixed rate, Total Gross Housing - variable rate, Total Gross Credit cards, Total Gross Revolving credit Total Margin lending Total Loans held for sale
Assets Loans And Receivables Revolving Credit Gross General Reserve for Credit Losses Amount
The general reserve for credit losses applying to the gross value of loans of a revolving credit nature, for a purpose other than housing.
Assets Loans And Receivables Revolving Credit Gross Of Provisions Denominated In AUD Amount

Total gross loans and advances denominated in Australian dollars (Gross of specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses) applying to the gross value of loans of a revolving credit nature, for a purpose other than housing.
Assets Loans And Receivables Revolving Credit Gross Of Provisions Denominated In Foreign Currency Amount

Total gross loans and advances denominated other than in Australian dollars (Gross of specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses) applying to the gross value of loans of a revolving credit nature, for a purpose other than housing.
Assets Loans And Receivables Revolving Credit Gross Specific Provisions Amount
The specific provisions for impairment applying to the gross value of loans of a revolving credit nature, for a purpose other than housing.
Assets Loans And Receivables Revolving Credit Gross Total Amount
The gross value of loans of a revolving credit nature, for a purpose other than housing, gross of any specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses.
ARF 320/321 A revolving credit is a loan arrangement in which the borrowing party may repay funds on loan and immediately borrow it again up to an agreed limit.
Assets Loans And Receivables Revolving Credit Margin Lending Collective Provisions Amount

Identify the component that is revolving credit facilities for the purpose of purchasing equities, where the underlying security is equities. Report the collective provision for this reporting line if this is recorded or allocated by the institution on this basis.
Assets Loans And Receivables Revolving Credit Margin Lending Gross Total Amount

Of the total reported for revolving credit, identify the component that is revolving credit facilities for the purpose of purchasing equities, where the underlying security is equities. This reporting item should be reported gross of any specific provisions and collective provision.
Assets Loans And Receivables Revolving Credit Margin Lending Specific Provisions Amount

Identify the component that is revolving credit facilities for the purpose of purchasing equities, where the underlying security is equities. Report the specific provisions applied to this loan item if this is recorded or allocated by the institution on this basis.
Assets Loans And Receivables Rural Producers Gross Amount

Record loans to rural producers. Use the following Australian and New Zealand Standard Industrial Classification (ANZSIC) categories: ANZSIC Types of Industry 011 Horticulture and Fruit Growing 012 Grain, Sheep and Beef Cattle Farming 013 Dairy Cattle Farming 014 Poultry Farming 015 Other Livestock Farming 016 Other Crop Growing 021 Services to Agriculture

Assets Loans And Receivables Term Loan Fixed Rate Gross Of Provisions Denominated In Foreign Currency Amount

Total gross loans and advances denominated other than in Australian dollars (Gross of specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses) applying to the gross value of fixed interest rate term loans.

The specific provisions for impairment applying to the gross value of fixed interest rate term loans.
Assets Loans And Receivables Term Loan Fixed Rate Gross Total Amount
The gross value of fixed interest rate term loans gross of any specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses.
Assets Loans And Receivables Term Loan Variable Rate Gross General Reserve For Credit Losses Amount
The general reserve for credit losses applying to the gross value of variable interest rate term loans.
Assets Loans And Receivables Term Loan Variable Rate Gross Specific Provisions Amount
The specific provisions for impairment applying to the gross value of variable interest rate term loans.
Assets Loans And Receivables Term Loan Variable Rate Gross Of Provisions Denominated in AUD Amount
Total gross loans and advances denominated in Australian dollars (Gross of specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses) applying to the gross value of variable interest rate term loans.
Assets Loans And Receivables Term Loan Variable Rate Gross Of Provisions Denominated in Foreign Currency Amount

Total gross loans and advances denominated other than in Australian dollars (Gross of specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses) applying to the gross value of variable interest rate term loans.
Assets Loans And Receivables Term Loan Variable Rate Gross Total Amount
The gross value of variable interest rate term loans gross of any specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial ADIs And Other Financial Institutions General Reserve For Credit Losses Amount
Report the General Reserve for Credit Losses applied to other commercial lending
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial ADIs And Other Financial Institutions Specific Provisions Amount

Report the specific provisions applied to other commercial lending. Where an ADI adopts a standardised approach under APS 220 (paragraph 11), as described in AGN 220.3, the value of the prescribed provision should also be included here.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial ADIs And Other Financial Institutions Total Amount

This reporting item should be brought to account at the gross value of the outstanding balance of the following loans: * treasury related short-term lending to other banks; * corporate banking customer relationship lending to other financial institutions; * loans and advances to other banks; * loans with banks and non-bank financial institutions; and * loans and advances to the parent entity, controlled entities, associated entities, joint venture entities and other branches under the same parent entity that are financial institutions. Report the balances applicable to the following counterparties * RBA - a public financial corporation and has responsibility for monetary policy, issuing banknotes, holding Australia's international reserves and providing banking services to the Commonwealth. * Other central bank institutions including APRA * Banks - refers to corporations, in relation to which an authority under subsection 9(3) is in force and which holds a consent under section 66 of the Banking Act 1959 to use the word bank; it includes development banks and foreign banks licensed to operate in Australia under the Banking Act 1959; but does not include merchant banks (record as non-bank financial intermediaries) and non-resident banks (report as non-resident counterparties). * Other ADIs - refers to corporations, in relation to which an authority under subsection 9(3) is in force, but which do not hold a consent under section 66 under the Banking Act 1959 to use the word bank. * RFCs - refers to corporations registered under the Financial Sector (Collection of Data) Act 2001 that are classified as Categories D and other and cash management trusts and includes money market corporations (also referred to as "merchant banks") (D); pastoral finance companies, finance companies and general financiers (Other); and cash management trusts. RFCs exclude intra group financiers registered under the Financial Sector (Collection of Data) Act 2001 Category I (record as private trading corporations). A list of corporations registered under the Financial Sector (Collection of Data) Act 2001 and their classification is available on request. * Central borrowing authorities (CBAs) - corporations established by State and Territory governments to provide finance for government authorities and to manage their surplus funds and includes New South Wales Treasury Corporation (NSW TCorp); Treasury Corporation of Victoria (TCV); Queensland Treasury Corporation (QTC); South Australian Government Financing Authority (SAFA); Western Australian Treasury Corporation (WATC); Tasmanian Public Finance Corporation (Tas Corp); Northern Territory Treasury Corporation (NT TCorp); and ACT Treasury. * Financial auxiliaries - corporations and quasi-corporations engaged primarily in activities closely related to financial intermediation, but which do not themselves perform an intermediation role including fund managers as principal;stockbrokers; and insurance brokers. * Securitisers - financial vehicles that issue short and/or long-term securities (called asset-backed securities) using specifically selected assets (e.g. mortgages, receivables). They provide backing (collateral) for the securities and generate the payment streams necessary to fulfil interest and principal requirements for investors. * Unit trusts - includes mortgage, fixed interest and equity unit trusts but excludes property and trading trusts. * Other financial intermediaries - all financial intermediaries other than central bank institutions, depository corporations, insurance corporations, pension funds, CBAs, securitisers and unit trusts. This includes economic development corporations owned by governments; co-operative housing societies; investment companies; and common funds including cash common funds.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Banks Collective Provisions Amount
Report the collective provision for loans to resident Australian banks if this is recorded or allocated by the institution on this basis.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Banks Gross Of Provisions Denominated in AUD Amount
Include the gross value of loans to banks that are denominated in Australian dollars.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Banks Gross Of Provisions Denominated in Foreign Currency Amount
Include the gross value of loans to banks that are denominated other than in Australian dollars.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Banks Specific Provisions Amount
Report the specific provisions for impairment applied to Australian and offshore banks.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Banks Total Amount
Include the gross value of loans to Australian and offshore banks. This reporting item should be reported gross of any specific provisions.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Central Borrowing Authorities Gross Of Provisions Denominated in AUD Amount
Include the gross value of loans to Australian central borrowing authorities that are denominated in Australian dollars.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Central Borrowing Authorities Gross Of Provisions Denominated in Foreign Currency Amount

Include settlement account balances due to Australian resident banks.
An Australian resident bank is a bank domiciled in Australia. Australian branches and Australian subsidiaries of foreign banks are regarded as resident banks.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Central Borrowing Authorities Total Amount
The gross value of loans to central borrowing authorities.

Central Borrowing Authorities (CBAs) - corporations established by State and Territory governments to provide finance for government authorities and to manage their surplus funds and includes New South Wales Treasury Corporation (NSW TCorp); Treasury Corporation of Victoria (TCV); Queensland Treasury Corporation (QTC); South Australian Government Financing Authority (SAFA); Western Australian Treasury Corporation (WATC); Tasmanian Public Finance Corporation (Tas Corp); Northern Territory Treasury Corporation (NT TCorp); and ACT Treasury.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Collective Provisions Total Amount
Report the aggregate collective provision for all commercial lending to residents.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Commonwealth Government Non Financial Corporations Gross Of Provisions Denominated in AUD Amount
Include the gross value of loans to Australian Commonwealth government non-financial corporations that are denominated in Australian dollars.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Commonwealth Government Non Financial Corporations Gross Of Provisions Denominated in Foreign Currency Amount
Include the gross value of loans to Australian Commonwealth government non-financial corporations that are denominated in other than Australian dollars.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Commonwealth Government Non Financial Corporations Amount
Include the gross value of loans to Australian Commonwealth government and foreign government non-financial corporations.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Community Service Organisations Non Profit Institutions Serving Households General Reserve For Credit Losses Amount
Report the General Reserve for Credit Losses applied to the total gross value of loans to Community Service Organisations.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Community Service Organisations Non Profit Institutions Serving Households Gross Of Provisions Denominated in AUD Amount

Include: * the total gross value of loans to community service organisations that are denominated in Australian dollars. This reporting item should be reported gross of any specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Community Service Organisations Non Profit Institutions Serving Households Gross Of Provisions Denominated In Foreign Currency Amount
The total amount of accumulated amortisation and impairment losses of intangible assets other than Information Technology (e.g. software) with a finite life.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Community Service Organisations Non Profit Institutions Serving Households Specific Provisions Amount
Report the specific provisions applied to total gross value of loans to Community Service Organisations.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Community Service Organisations Non Profit Institutions Serving Households Total Amount

Include the total gross value of loans to Australian and offshore community service organisations. This reporting item should be reported gross of any specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses.

Community Service Organisations (CSOs) include: * institutions financed mostly by members' contributions, e.g. trade unions, professional societies, consumer associations, political parties, churches and religious societies, and social, cultural, recreational and sports clubs; and * charities and aid organisations financed by voluntary transfers. Exclude: * CSOs and non-profit institutions controlled and mainly financed by government (include in general government).

The specific provisions for impairment applying to the gross value of credit cards to other than households.
Assets Loans And Receivables Commercial Credit Cards Amount
The gross value of credit cards to other than households gross of any specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses.

Report the specific provisions for impairment applied to credit cards. Where an ADI adopts a standardised approach under APS 220 (paragraph 11), as described in AGN 220.3, the value of the prescribed provision should also be included here.
Assets Loans And Receivables Households Personal Credit Cards Total Amount
Include the gross value of credit card liabilities by householders. This reporting item should be reported gross of any specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses.
Assets Loans And Receivables Households Personal Leasing General Reserve For Credit Losses Amount
Report the General Reserve for Credit Losses applied to lease financing to households.
Assets Loans And Receivables Households Personal Leasing Specific Provisions Amount

Report the specific provisions for impairment applied to lease financing to households. Where an ADI adopts a standardised approach under APS 220 (paragraph 11), as described in AGN 220.3, the value of the prescribed provision should also be included here.
Assets Loans And Receivables Households Personal Leasing Total Amount
Total gross loans to households representing lease financing is reported net of unearned revenue and gross of provisions.
Assets Loans And Receivables Households Personal Revolving Credit General Reserve For Credit Losses Amount
Report the General Reserve for Credit Losses applied to revolving credit to households other than credit cards or loans originally approved for housing.
Assets Loans And Receivables Households Personal Revolving Credit Secured By Residential Mortgage Specific Provisions Amount

Report the specific provisions for impairment applied to loans secured by residential mortgage of a revolving credit nature to householders, other than credit cards, or loans originally approved for a purpose other than housing.
Assets Loans And Receivables Households Personal Revolving Credit Secured By Residential Mortgage Amount

Of the total reported for loans of a revolving credit nature to householders, other than credit cards, or loans originally approved for a purpose other than housing, identify the component that is revolving credit secured by residential mortgage. This reporting item should be reported gross of any specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses.
Assets Loans And Receivables Households Personal Revolving Credit Specific Provisions Amount

Report the specific provisions for impairment applied to revolving credit to households other than credit cards or loans originally approved for housing. Where an ADI adopts a standardised approach under APS 220 (paragraph 11), as described in AGN 220.3, the value of the prescribed provision should also be included here.
Assets Loans And Receivables Households Personal Revolving Credit Total Amount

Include the gross value of loans of a revolving credit nature to householders, other than credit cards, or loans originally approved for a purpose other than housing. This reporting item should be reported gross of any specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses.
Revolving credit is a loan arrangement in which the borrowing party may repay funds on loan and immediately borrow it again up to an agreed limit.
Assets Loans And Receivables Households Specific Provisions Against Housing Total Amount

Report the specific provision for impairment applied to all housing loans. Where the reporting party adopts a standardised approach under APS 220 (paragraph 11), as described in AGN 220.3 Prescribed Provisioning (AGN 220.3), the value of the prescribed provision should also be included here.
Assets Loans And Receivables Households Specific Provisions Total Amount
The specific provisions for impairment applying to the gross value of total loans to household.

Provisions assessed on an individual facility basis in accordance with the Australian equivalents to International Financial Reporting Standards (IFRS) are to be treated as specific provisions in the reporting forms for regulatory reporting purposes (Prudential Standard APS 220 Credit Quality (APS 220)). Specific provisions also include that portion of provisions assessed on a collective basis that are not eligible for regulatory purposes to be included in General Reserve for Credit Losses as defined by APS 220.
Assets Loans And Receivables Households Total Amount
The gross value of total loans to household gross of any specific provisions and General Reserve for Credit Losses.

Households comprises individuals, or groups of individuals, whose dealings with other sectors are for personal or household purposes. Excludes family trusts, sole proprietors, partnerships and any other unincorporated enterprises owned by households.
